site_name: Phase 5 Of The Acton Gardens Masterplan, Site Comprising

protected_spaces_details.description: Provision for children and young people

description: Reserved matters application for Phase 5 of the Acton Gardens masterplan detailing Landscaping, Appearance, Scale, Access and Layout in relation to the construction of four apartment buildings varying between five-storeys, seven storeys, nine storeys and twelve storeys high containing 271 new residential units (76 one-bed, 143 two bed, 45 three bed, 7 four bed); associated private and semi-private amenity space, refuse/recycling and bicycle storage; energy plant rooms, 48 off-street and 34 on-street car parking spaces; works to the public highway and public realm improvements, following the demolition of Conrad Tower, Carroll Court, Meredith Tower and Galsworthy Court; application made part pursuant to conditions 2 (Reserved Matters), 4 (Reserved Matters Details), 5 (Details of Public Realm Landscaping), 6 (Energy Strategy), 11 (Noise Mitigation Measures), 13 (Air Pollution Mitigation Measures), 16 (Flood Risk Assessment), 18 (Tree Protection), 19 (Refuse and Recycling Enclosures), 20 (Archaeological Investigation), 22 (Rainwater and / or Greywater Recycling Systems), 25 (Boundary Treatments), 26 (Details of Secured by Design) of outline planning permission LBE ref: P/2012/0708, dated 13/08/2013 (amended by minor material amendment application PP/2014/2142, dated 21/07/2014) for the multi-Phased regeneration of the South Acton Estate.
